name: Warm up for 5-6 minutes with some light movement.
des: Before you start your home cardio routine, get your blood pumping for a few minutes and warm up your muscles.

name: Do 2 sets of 15-24 rocket jumps
des: Rocket jumps are a fun and exhilarating way to start your workout! Put your feet hip-width apart and bend your knees slightly. Bend down and put your hands on your thighs.

name: Get your whole body moving with 2 sets of star jumps
des: Star jumps are similar to jumping jacks, but with the twist that you do them while airborne.

name: Exercise your lower body with some squats
des: Squats are a good cardio workout, and they’re also great for toning your back, legs, and rear. To do squats, start with your feet shoulder width apart

name: Work out your arms and legs with 2 sets of tap backs
des: This is a fun workout that feels a bit like a dance move. Stand up straight and step back with your right foot while swinging your arms straight out in front of you at the same time.

name: Wrap it up with some burpees
des: Start out in a standing position, then drop down into a squat and put your hands on the ground in front of you.

name: Cool down with some gentle stretches
des: When you’re done, cool down for at least 5 minutes to help your heart return to a resting rate gradually.

name: Mix up your routine by getting outside if you can
des: Getting out of the house can boost your mood and make exercising more fun.

name: Watch a cardio warmup video if it helps you to follow along
des: Watching a coach or instructor go through a workout routine can make it easier to set a good pace and get the workout you need.
